    "card_no": '4',
    "term":' <p><strong>A 70-year-old patient with an IgG lambda MGUS undergoes a kidney biopsy for proteinuria. The patient has a hematoma and excessive bleeding after the biopsy. His PT and PTT were both elevated. 1:1 mixing study corrects to normal immediately and remains corrected after 1-hour incubation</strong>.</p><div class="box-purple-border"><strong>What is the likely diagnosis?<br/> What is the underlying etiology?</strong></div>',
